Sentencas: The performance of a novel micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) with an inert support and an integrated current collector for the inner electrode was improved by controlling its microstructural features.
Titulo: Performance improvement and redox cycling of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell with a porous zirconia support

Sentencas: Multi-step dip coating and co-sintering methods were used to fabricate the cell containing porous yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ), Ni, Ni-YSZ, YSZ, strontium-doped lanthanum manganite (LSM)-YSZ, and LSM as the inert support, anode current collector, anode, electrolyte, cathode, and cathode current collector, respectively.
Titulo: Performance improvement and redox cycling of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell with a porous zirconia support

Sentencas: To enhance gas diffusion through the YSZ support by properly tailoring its porosity, a combination of micro-crystalline cellulose and polymethyl methacrylate pore formers was used.
Titulo: Performance improvement and redox cycling of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell with a porous zirconia support

Sentencas: Additionally, the porosity of the Ni current collector was improved and the LSM-YSZ cathode was sufficiently thick for high oxygen reduction activity.
Titulo: Performance improvement and redox cycling of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell with a porous zirconia support

Sentencas: Owing to its optimized microstructure, the micro-tubular SOFC delivered excellent power output with maximum power densities of 710, 591, 445, and 316 mW cm(-2) at 850, 800, 750, and 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Performance improvement and redox cycling of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell with a porous zirconia support

Sentencas: The effect of redox cycling on cell performance was investigated by alternately exposing the anode to fuel and air atmospheres.
Titulo: Performance improvement and redox cycling of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell with a porous zirconia support

Sentencas: The cell had good tolerance toward the redox phenomenon with no apparent degradation in its performance up to 10 redox cycles.
Titulo: Performance improvement and redox cycling of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell with a porous zirconia support
